Author : Olivier Koch, olivier@olivierkoch.org
Date : July 2016


DESCRIPTION
------------------------------------------
Nestor is an assistant that displays weather conditions and public transport live schedules on a screen.

It is currently setup for buses an metros in Paris, but you can include your own source of data.


INSTALLATION
------------------------------------------
Copy the code in a local directory and run nestor.sh


DEPENDENCIES
------------------------------------------
python >= 2.7
Pillow
python-tk
python-imaging-tk
xte (to simulate key presses)

